# Packages the Blueberry base system already provides.
# When bpm resolves dependencies (e.g. from the official Arch repos), any dep
# named here is treated as satisfied and is NOT downloaded/installed — this
# keeps Arch packages from trying to reinstall glibc, bash, coreutils, etc.
# over the base system. One package name per line; #comments and blanks ignored.
#
# A built-in list lives in `is_provided` inside the bpm script; this file EXTENDS
# it. Add anything else your image bundles (e.g. ncurses, zlib if you ship them).
ncurses
zlib
